      <section eId="sec_CCP-3661">
        <num>CCP 3661</num>
        <heading>3661.  Same; title not at issue; limited admissibility of evidence of title</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3661__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In the possessory action, the ownership or title of the parties to the immovable
property or real right therein is not at issue.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3661__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>No evidence of ownership or title to the immovable property or real right therein
shall be admitted except to prove any of the following:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-3661__subsec_B__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The possession thereof by a party as owner.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-3661__subsec_B__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The extent of the possession thereof by a party and his ancestors in title.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-3661__subsec_B__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The length of time in which a party and his ancestors in title have had possession
thereof.
Amended by</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111827</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
